  <abstract>Enrique Reye interviews Jaime Oyarzun, Presidente de Casa Chile. A Chilean musical play entitled La Pergola y las flores written by Isadora Aguirre and Franciso Flores del Campo is presented. The play is about a young Chilean farm girl who takes the train to Santiago from her southern home town of San Rosendo. Sergio Lacayo, ambassador of Nicaragua in Canada, discusses the peace plan and the Sandinista government's reaction to the United States recent intervention in Central America. Variety of Latin American music is presented.</abstract>
